Program: Discovery
Title: Water Works - Danube River
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jryds
Last Broadcast Date: 27 May 2003
An examination of the efforts to clean up the Danube River and rebuild the bridges at Novi Sad, Serbia. The bridges were destroyed during by NATO forces during war in the former Yugoslavia. The programme looks at the clearance work being carried out before a rebuilding programme can begin. Presenter: Julian Siddle. Show less